<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="222" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,727,752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[326,613,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[326,613,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Hemerodromia juanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[624,718,727,752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[624,718,727,752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[883,1081,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cercusdilatata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[883,1081,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">H. cercusdilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1093,1187,727,752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1093,1187,727,752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by T 
<number box="[1259,1269,728,752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
without basal denticle; subepandrial sclerite with 
<number box="[547,561,764,788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
finger-like posterior processes; and membranous hypandrium. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Hemerodromia juanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[266,357,799,824]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[266,357,799,824]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from latter by cercus narrow, with a short finger-like process bearing a long spine and bluntly pointed subapical process incurved; and phallus with two lateral and two ventral flattened plates and a dorsal process apically. In 
<taxonomicName box="[446,638,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cercusdilatata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[446,638,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">H. cercusdilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[645,734,871,896]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[645,734,871,896]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the cercus is greatly enlarged and phallus is sclerotized basally with membranous area covered with small spicules apically.
</paragraph>
